The paper discusses a new approach for single-particle cryo-electron microscopy (cryo-EM) that involves directly reconstructing the 3-D structure from micrographs without intermediate detection. This involves a mathematical model and autocorrelation analysis technique, which are likely to fall under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses numerical results and challenges, which could fall under numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper is related to microscopy (cs.MM), which is another possible sub-category.
